text: Wilbraham Fens is a 62.5 hectare biological Site of Special Scientific Interest east of Cambridge. This is an example of a fen habitat, which is now rare in Britain, with grassland, scrub, ponds and ditches. The dominant fen species is common reed, which is present in dense stands, together with plants such as purple loosestrife and meadow rue. Herbs include harebell and field scabious. There is no public access but the site can be viewed from footpaths. ==References== Category:Sites of Special Scientific Interest in Cambridgeshire
